    "publishDate": "10 May 2024",
    "excerpt": "How a small family business escaped foreclosure and achieved a fixed monthly income of $4,500 through strategic refinancing.",
    "content": "From the brink of bankruptcy action, our client now enjoys a fixed monthly income …\n\nTHE BACKGROUND\n\nThe client runs a small family business importing and exporting goods from neighbouring ASEAN countries. It has been doing this for 35 years. Being old school, he runs his business based on relationships and personal ties. He has used the same bank for all his financial needs over the last 45 years. Conservative in his borrowing, he has one commercial loan secured by a mortgage over his shop house and a renovation loan (surprisingly, this was in the form of an overdraft facility) secured by his home.\n\nTHE PROBLEM\n\nDuring the economic slowdown, his business took a hit, and cash flow became a problem. The client started to miss loan repayment instalments, which amounted to $15,000 per month, and he paid them intermittently whenever he could. Each month, he struggled to raise the funds required to pay the loan instalments, which were overdue. Snowballing default interest became impossible, overshadowing his anxiety over his failing business.\n\nWHY HE CAME TO SEE US\n\nBy the time he came to see us, he had received a letter of demand from his bank. They had threatened to foreclose on both loans. In addition, the bank's employee, who had served as his relationship manager over the last twenty years, had recently left the bank. The new relationship manager taking over his account was not sympathetic - \"new brooms sweep client,\" as the saying goes - the new manager's prevailing concern was to reduce the bank's exposure in a recession.\n\nHaving been backed into a corner and feeling overwhelmed, the client came to see us, not expecting any more in terms of legal services than to help him \"buy\" some time with the bank. Yet, at the same time, he was desperately looking for ways to raise the funds to stave off the repossession of his family home.\n\nWHAT WE ACHIEVED\n\nA quick investigation of our client's borrowing history and current property valuations showed that –\n1. his residential property is valued at $2.3 million, and his shophouse is valued at $1.1 million (current valuations).\n2. the client's total debt to the bank is $900k, a mere fraction of the total worth of the mortgaged properties - our client was over-securitized!\n\nWe called our bankers, and within a few days, they offered to refinance his loan by giving him a NEW term loan secured by his residential property only.\n\nAs residential term loans bear much lower interest rates than overdraft loans, the client's liability to his new bankers was now reduced to a manageable $2,500 per month.\n\nOur client was so relieved and heartened by his status change that he could now focus on his business. To help him ride out the recession, he was able to sub-let his shophouse for $7,000 per month.\n\nAs a result, from the brink of bankruptcy action, our client now enjoys a fixed monthly income of $4,500!\n\nRefinancing will help you reduce your monthly repayments and improve your quality of life.",
    "imageUrl": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1573164713714-d95e436ab8d6?q=80&w=800&auto=format&fit=crop",
    "titleZh": "濒临破产：意外的转机",
    "excerptZh": "一个小家族企业如何通过战略性再融资避免丧失抵押品赎回权并获得 4,500 美元的固定月收入。",
    "contentZh": "从濒临破产的境地，我们的客户现在享有固定的月收入……\n\n背景\n\n客户经营着一家小型家族企业，从邻近的东盟国家进出口商品。这项业务已经经营了 35 年。作为一个老派的人，他的生意建立在关系和私人纽带之上。在过去的 45 年里，他的所有财务需求都使用同一家银行。他在借贷方面很保守，有一笔以店屋为抵押的商业贷款，以及一笔以房屋为抵押的装修贷款（令人惊讶的是，这是一种透支形式）。\n\n问题\n\n在经济放缓期间，他的生意受到了冲击，现金流出现了问题。客户开始拖欠每月 15,000 美元的贷款分期付款，只能断断续续地偿还。每个月，他都在努力筹集资金支付逾期的贷款分期付款。滚雪球般的违约利息变得难以承受，掩盖了他对生意失败的焦虑。\n\n他为什么来找我们\n\n当他来找我们时，已经收到了银行的催款信。银行威胁要取消这两笔贷款的抵押品赎回权。此外，过去二十年一直担任通过客户经理的银行员工最近离职了。接管他账户的新客户经理并不同情——俗话说“新官上任三把火”——新经理的主要关注点可以减少银行在经济衰退中的风险敞口。\n\n被逼入绝境且感到不知所措的客户来找我们，并不指望我们能提供什么法律服务，只是希望能帮他向银行“争取”一些时间。然而，与此同时，通过他也在拼命寻找筹集资金的方法，以避免家庭住房被收回。\n\n我们取得的成果\n\n对各户借贷历史和当前房产估值的快速调查显示：\n1. 他的住宅房产估值为 230 万美元，店屋估值为 110 万美元（当前估值）。\n2. 客户欠银行的总债务为 90 万美元，仅占抵押房产总价值的一小部分——我们的客户被过度证券化了！\n\n我们联系了我们的银行家，几天之内，他们提出通过为他提供仅以其住宅房产为抵押的新定期贷款来为他的贷款再融资。\n\n由于住宅定期贷款的利率远低于透支贷款，客户对新银行家的负债现在减少到了可控的每月 2,500 美元。\n\n客户对自己的状况变化感到非常欣慰和振奋，他现在可以专注于自己的生意了。为了帮助他度过经济衰退，他得以以每月 7,000 美元的价格转租了他的店屋。\n\n结果，从濒临破产的境地，我们的客户现在享有每月 4,500 美元的固定收入！\n\n再融资将帮助您减少每月还款额并提高生活质量。"
